N/A

I can recommend it. This game is fun.
The Good:
+ Not a bad game, easy to play;
+ Beautiful art and sound;
+ Low CPU usage;
+ Control either with your mouse or a microphone.

The Bad:
- Game is about 1.5-2 hours long.

If you're wondering password 16 lvl:
SOS

Pros:
- Decent art style, hand-drawn visuals and pleasant ambient;
- Original gameplay that allows you to play using your voice. If not, you can still play with a mouse.

Cons:
- The game is very short (~2 hours);
- The plot is rather an excuse, and it suggests you (what a shame!) to act as a streikbrecher;
- No exit button (irritating).

The verdict:
I've bought it on a sale for $0.11 and have nothing to regret. Still, I don't recommend to buy it for more than this price.

